verses.roman:
āra eka adbhuta gopī-bhāvera svabhāva
buddhira gocara nahe yāhāra prabhāva

synonyms: āra—another; eka—one; adbhuta—wonderful; gopī-bhāvera—of the emotion of the gopīs; svabhāva—nature; buddhira—of the intelligence; gocara—an object of perception; nahe—is not; yāhāra—of which; prabhāva—the power.
translation: There is another wonderful feature of the emotion of the gopīs. Its power is beyond the comprehension of the intelligence.
